                        <h2>Do I have to respond to the census?</h2>   
                            <p>By taking part in the rehearsal, you'll help us with our preparations for the census in 2021. You don't have to but, if you’ve been invited, we’d be grateful if you did. Testing our processes will help us make sure the census in 2021 is easier to do and better for everyone. We can only do this if people take part in the rehearsal. If you live in one of the four areas where we’re carrying out the rehearsal, we’ll ask you to fill in the online questionnaire. The areas are:</p> 
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Carlisle</li>
                                    <li>Ceredigion</li>
                                    <li>Hackney</li>
                                    <li>Tower Hamlets</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p>It’s important you get involved. The more people who respond, the better the information we’ll have to help us plan for 2021. We’ll send you an invite letter if we need you to take part. It won’t take long to do – we’re talking around 20 minutes in total.</p>
